radiographic_examinations.findings: Mild bibasilar atelectasis; diffusely low liver attenuation consistent with hepatic steatosis; no focal hepatic lesions; normal gallbladder, spleen, pancreas, and adrenal glands; subcentimeter hypodensities in the right kidney; normal appearing small bowel; large bowel grossly unremarkable with slight hyperenhancing wall of appendix and adjacent fat stranding; no pathologically enlarged lymph nodes; minimal free fluid in the pelvis.
